<seg id="16">For electronics, we were happy with that tape recorder of mum’s and, at the most, a Walkman which I shared with my sister and which, by the way, we only used on the train on a school trip.</seg>
<seg id="17">We thought it was more interesting to play Flying Hats or Ludo with our aunt, or as I said before, "just" go outside.</seg>
<seg id="18">When I was a bit older, we got a video recorder under the Christmas tree, which my parents had clearly saved for for a long time, but unfortunately it did not last long with us.</seg>
